dp-service â€” Release Artifacts and Verification
===============================================

This repository publishes the dp-service backend as a self-contained executable JAR
via GitHub Releases.

Each release corresponds to a Git tag of the form:

  rel-<version>

Example:
  rel-1.12.0-rc8

------------------------------------------------------------
Release Contents
------------------------------------------------------------

Each release contains:

  dp-service-<version>.jar
    Executable service JAR (fat / shaded).

  dp-service-<version>.jar.sha256
    SHA-256 checksum for integrity verification.

------------------------------------------------------------
Download and Installation
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Download the JAR and checksum from the GitHub Release page.

2. Verify the checksum:

   sha256sum -c dp-service-<version>.jar.sha256

   The output should indicate:
     dp-service-<version>.jar: OK

3. Run the service:

   java -jar dp-service-<version>.jar

------------------------------------------------------------
Configuration
------------------------------------------------------------

Runtime configuration is provided via external files, typically:

  application.yml
  log4j2.xml

These are supplied by the data-platform installer or deployment environment.

------------------------------------------------------------
Notes
------------------------------------------------------------

- dp-service depends on dp-grpc APIs.
- The service is designed to be run as part of the Data Platform distribution.
